		<description><![CDATA[[O]ne must take heed that we be not excessively lengthy here [i.e., in doctrinal argument], and steal away our time from application, which is the soul of preaching. —Petrus van Mastricht, The Best Method of Preaching, trans. Todd Rester (Grand Rapids, MI: Reformation Heritage Books, 2013), 46.]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<blockquote><p><a href="http://www.heritagebooks.org/the-best-method-of-preaching/"><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-468" alt="The Best Method of Preaching — Petrus van Mastricht" src="https://dash.dedeo.tk/wp-content/uploads/Mascricht_Best_Method_Preaching.jpg" width="175" height="257" /></a>[O]ne must take heed that we be not excessively lengthy here [i.e., in doctrinal argument], and steal away our time from application, which is the soul of preaching.</p></blockquote>
<p style="text-align: right;">—Petrus van Mastricht, <a href="http://www.heritagebooks.org/the-best-method-of-preaching/"><em>The Best Method of Preaching</em></a>, trans. Todd Rester<br />
(Grand Rapids, MI: Reformation Heritage Books, 2013), 46.</p>
